body:
It would increase clarity for the language if slice literals could be expressed without an explicit type.
https://play.golang.org/p/HT1d0hrrhj

This could be done for any literal slices which contain constants.
eg.
```
{"a", "b", "c"} => []string{"a", "b", "c"}
{1, 2, 3}       => []int{1, 2, 3}
{2.0, 3.0, 1.2} => []float64{2, 3, 1.2}
```

A statement such as
var array = {1, 2, 3, 4}

Would be clean and understandable.
